```typescript
const addressSchema = z.object({
  fullName: z.string().min(3, { message: "Nom complet requis (min 3 caractères)" }),
  addressLine: z.string().min(5, { message: "Adresse trop courte" }),
  city: z.string().min(2, { message: "Ville invalide" }),
  postalCode: z.string().regex(/^\d{5}$/, { message: "Code postal à 5 chiffres" }),
  country: z.string().min(2, { message: "Pays requis" }),
  phone: z.string().optional(),
});

type AddressForm = z.infer<typeof addressSchema>;

const { register, handleSubmit, formState: { errors } } = useForm<AddressForm>({
  resolver: zodResolver(addressSchema)
});
```
Chaque champ est validé : postalCode avec expression régulière, fullName avec longueur minimale, etc. ZodResolver connecte le schéma à React Hook Form.

```typescript
import { create } from 'zustand';
import { persist } from 'zustand/middleware';

interface DeliveryState {
  shippingAddress: any | null;
  setAddress: (address: any) => void;
}

export const useDeliveryStore = create<DeliveryState>()(
  persist(
    (set) => ({
      shippingAddress: null,
      setAddress: (address) => set({ shippingAddress: address }),
    }),
    { name: 'delivery-storage' }
  )
);
```
Après validation du formulaire, on appelle `setAddress(data)`. Au prochain chargement, `shippingAddress` sera restauré.
